# Dirty Pipe Vulnerability (CVE-2022-0904)

The **Dirty Pipe** vulnerability allows writing to a file without triggering the copy-on-write (CoW) protection, enabling arbitrary file writes. This bypasses the normal write path and can be exploited to inject data into files that are open for reading.

